format:
<style>
  .filled { 
      height: 100% !important;

      padding: 0 !important;
      margin: 0 !important;
  }
  .nr-dashboard-template {
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
  }
  
  .rounded {
  border-radius: 12px 12px 12px 12px;
}
 
   .bigfont {
  font-size: 18px;
}

   .smallfont {
  font-size: 12px;
}
  
</style>

<script>
$('.vibrate').on('click', function() {
  navigator.vibrate(100);
});

function restore_bg(x) {
            $(this).css("background-color", x);
    };

$('.touched').on('mousedown', function() {
    
    var x= $(this).css("background-color");
    $(this).css("background-color", "yellow");
    
    setTimeout(restore_bg.bind(this,x),100);
    navigator.vibrate(80);
    });
    
</script>

Change Group Name
format:
<script>
(function($scope) {
$scope.oldGroupName = 'TEMP' // initial group placeholder name

$scope.$watch('msg', function() {
    if ($scope.msg){
        $("p.nr-dashboard-cardtitle").each(function(){
            if($(this).text().trim() == $scope.oldGroupName.trim()){
                p = $(this);
                p.text($scope.msg.payload);
                 $scope.oldGroupName = $scope.msg.payload
            }
        })
    }
 });
})(scope);
</script>

name: Get only updated values in msg.payload
Always updates when messages comes msg.payload
msg.40004 is updated with the payload msg.40004_raw contains all json info
msg.payload is updated with the request.
Input node, first output only updates when the value is changed, the second output always updates, msg.raw contains the whole JSON with more information
Request node, request a updated value from the heatpump, the first output will add the message to msg.40004 (example), the second output adds it to the msg.payload
Confirmation from the heatpump that the message has been ACKED and the new value is returned
Output node, sets the selected register to the value in msg.payload
Unnamed node gets all the updates from every register that has been added or in the LOG.SET
Every value, the same or not
Confirmation from the heatpump that the message has been ACKED and the new value is returned
No name in output node takes register from msg.topic, and the value from msg.payload

The MQTT Broker is running at 127.0.0.1:1883 with no auth.
In the input node, you can easily add registers by checking the box, NibePi will request them regulary, the more registers added, the longer it will take for each message.
